tafsir[11]{c,v,t}:
  75,21,"(And neglect the Hereafter) and neglect working for the reward of the Hereafter."
  75,23,"(Looking towards their Lord) they behold the Countenance of their Lord and are not veiled from Him;"
  75,25,"(Thou wilt know) those faces will know (that some great disaster is about to fall on them) a severe and horrible punishment is about to befall them."
  75,27,"(And men say) and those around it among his family and others say: (Where is the wizard (who can save him now)?) Is there any physician who can cure him? It is also said this means: the angels say to one another: who will rise with his soul to Allah?"
  75,28,"(And he knowth) and the dead person knows at that point (that it is the parting) the time of departing from the life of the world;"
  75,29,"(And agony is heaped on agony) and severity is heaped upon severity: the severity of the last day of the life of the world and that of the first day of the Hereafter; and it is also said this means: and the dead person's legs are twisted around each other;"
  75,30,"(Unto thy Lord that day) the Day of Judgement (will be the driving) the return of all created beings."
  75,32,"(But he denied) Allah's divine Oneness (and flouted) and turned away from faith."
  75,33,"(Then went he to his folk) in the life of the world (with glee) strutting and behaving wantonly."
  75,37,"(Was he not) i.e. Abu Jahl (a drop of fluid) man's sperm drops (which gushed forth) in the woman's womb; and it is also said: created in the woman's womb?"
  76,4,"(Lo! We have prepared for disbelievers) Abu Jahl and his followers (manacles and carcans) in the Fire (and a raging fire."